# Trivy ignore file — CVEs suppressed with justification
# Format: CVE-ID  # reason | reviewed: YYYY-MM-DD | next review: YYYY-MM-DD
#
# Rule: only suppress when the vulnerability does not apply to our runtime usage
# and no immediate remediation path exists through our codebase.

# tar (npm internal dependency — node:18-alpine bundled npm)
# tar is used by npm itself for package extraction, not by our application code.
# Our app does not extract archives at runtime — attack vector requires a malicious
# archive to be passed to tar.extract(), which never happens in our code path.
# Remediation path: upgrade base image to node:20-alpine when LTS support allows.
CVE-2026-23745  # tar in bundled npm, not app code | reviewed: 2026-06-10 | next review: 2026-09-10
